<br>
1. We port up invised, it doesn't work on everything but somethings it does, if it wears off on the way to safe spot just stand there and die, do not train the SS.<br>
<br>
2. Resists for PoH are not needed, only thing I have been in counter with that has an AoE is Maestro of Rancor which is Life Tap which is nearly unresistable.<br>
<br>
3. Have clip plane down for lag, serverfilteron, Spell effects off, Partical effects off, PC and NPC names off.<br>
<br>
4. Raid fees go to me.<br>
<br>
5. If we take down Maestro, The hand of Maestro's drop for warrior epic are taken.<br>
<br>
6. To get to SS (safe spot) take all rights out of the port in area, follow with the wall on the left, come to a corner then take a right, stop when you get to about loc n262, p370.<br>
<br>
7. Spite Golems, and all other golems in PoH are unmezzable and about 99% resistant to magic, cant be snared.<br>
<br>
8. There will be a designated snarer, preferable highest level druid or really high level Ranger.<br>
<br>
9. At the SS dont go up more than a little ways up the wall, you could agro 2nd floor which is very uncool I have seen it happen.<br>
<br>
10. Dont use AoE's, just like on number 9, you could agro 2nd floor as it has happened in the past.<br>
<br>
11. If we have a magician able to summon, we will summon across Hate to spot for Maestro pull.<br>
<br>
12. Seems we already have a rezzing necro on list wanting to go, we will have a necro, rogue, monk, cleric, the porting Wizard, and another in first port up group. So if you die a rogue or monk could drag your corpse to SS. And if the cleric makes it there alive the cleric can rez you, if not the necro will rez the cleric to start the rezzing.<br>
<br>
13. There are a few wandering mobs from port in spot to SS that will see invis, remember if you get agro stand there and die, do not  train SS.<br>
<br>
14. If we have a HUGE turnout for this we may move up to 2nd floor as long as we have a very experience puller, this is unlikely though so we will basically just do 1st floor.<br>
<br>
15. Raid is supposed to last at least 8 or so hours if not longer, if you wish to leave early you will be TLed out by one of our wizzys, /wink /wink Kelios.<br>
<br>
16. If you do not assist on a pull you will be given a warning, if you do it again you will be TLed out no questions asked.<br>
<br>
17. Death is inevitable in a raid like this, expect to die not once but many times.<br>
<br>
18. Forgot to mention, didn't count cost of peridots in raid fee, now up to 75pp raid fee sorry all.<br>
<br>
19. Since we will have many druids I will assign a druid on first snare and if that druid dies then another will take over.<br>
<br>
20. Cant get this link thing to work so I suggest going to EQmaps.com and looking at PoH there, and go to Allakazams for strategies and such.<br>
<br>
21. I will shout rules and strategies when we get to SRo.<br>
<br>
22. Have fun, this is the all time meaning of  raids, just go and have fun.<br>
<br>
